               </text>
            </section>
            <section>
               <title value="Hospital course note"/>
               <code>
                  <coding>
                     <system value="http://loinc.org"/>
                     <code value="8648-8"/>
                     <display value="Hospital course note"/>
                  </coding>
               </code>
               <text>
                  <status value="generated"/>
                  <div xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Dear colleague, I am writing to inform you regarding your patient, an 81-year-old male admitted under our care for severe aortic valve stenosis. Upon admission, echocardiographic assessment confirmed critical aortic stenosis with significantly reduced valve area and elevated mean transvalvular gradient. Given his symptomatic presentation and the severity of findings, the patient was evaluated by our multidisciplinary heart team. Following careful risk stratification and cardiac catheterization, he underwent successful surgical aortic valve replacement without perioperative complications. Post-operative recovery was uneventful, with satisfactory haemodynamic parameters on discharge. Current medication adjustments have been made accordingly, and I kindly request continued follow-up including wound inspection, anticoagulation monitoring, and cardiac rehabilitation referral. Please do not hesitate to contact us should any concerns arise. With collegial regards.</div>
               </text>
            </section>
